title: Microsoft Azure Firewall: Throughput
agents: azure_v2
catalog: cloud/azure
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the throughput of Microsoft Azure Firewalls. It reports
 the amount of data processed by the firewall in bytes per second.

 You can configure warning and critical levels using the rule
 "Azure Firewall Throughput".

 In order to use this check, you need to configure the Azure special agent.

discovery:
 One service is created for each Azure Firewall.
